dditive Roman numerals of four in sequence are common and preferred in insc=
riptions, like on clocks). It appears that in Roman numerals, each decimal =
place digit must be written out in a hole. So, for example,999 could be log=
ically written as IM but it=E2=80=99s not. Each digit in the number 999 has=
